478
00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:51.320
A Marine ship is flying through the sky!

479
00:18:51.320 --> 00:18:53.990
Why?! How is that possible?!

480
00:18:53.990 --> 00:18:55.320
Who's on it?!

481
00:18:56.780 --> 00:18:59.700
Isn't it... falling toward us?

482
00:18:59.700 --> 00:19:02.250
R-Run!

483
00:19:05.960 --> 00:19:07.080
Look!

484
00:19:07.080 --> 00:19:08.590
On the ship!

485
00:19:11.380 --> 00:19:14.840
No way! I thought he retired!

486
00:19:15.340 --> 00:19:16.800
The legendary...

487
00:19:16.800 --> 00:19:18.390
Hero!

488
00:19:23.520 --> 00:19:26.480
Vice Admiral Garp!

489
00:19:26.980 --> 00:19:28.480
Koby!

490
00:19:28.480 --> 00:19:30.480
I'm here to save you!

491
00:19:32.230 --> 00:19:34.990
Run! Just run!

492
00:19:34.990 --> 00:19:35.950
We can't...

493
00:19:35.950 --> 00:19:37.910
There's no way out!

494
00:19:41.490 --> 00:19:45.040
Hey, you damn pirates!

495
00:19:45.870 --> 00:19:48.000
He's coming! Run!

496
00:20:06.890 --> 00:20:08.770
Vice Admiral Garp...

497
00:20:09.810 --> 00:20:12.900
Why? I'm not even worth saving...

498
00:20:13.320 --> 00:20:14.900
You idiots!

499
00:20:15.610 --> 00:20:20.870
Do you have any idea who
the hell you've kidnapped?!

500
00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:32.170
Koby is the future of the Marines!

501
00:20:33.340 --> 00:20:35.960
Not to mention...

502
00:20:36.420 --> 00:20:40.550
my precious protégé!

503
00:20:41.930 --> 00:20:45.220
Galaxy...

504
00:20:56.400 --> 00:21:00.280
Impact!

505
00:21:59.090 --> 00:22:01.630
Cumulo-glorpus!

506
00:22:14.600 --> 00:22:16.610
Damn you, Garp!

507
00:22:16.610 --> 00:22:18.190
He's insane!

508
00:22:18.190 --> 00:22:20.440
I'll make that geezer pay!

509
00:22:20.440 --> 00:22:22.150
Don't move, pirates!

510
00:22:23.110 --> 00:22:26.870
Resistance will only result in further damage!

511
00:22:33.870 --> 00:22:36.380
Absolutely pathetic...

512
00:22:37.170 --> 00:22:39.170
I've really gotten rusty.

513
00:22:39.800 --> 00:22:41.170
Screw you!

514
00:22:41.170 --> 00:22:43.800
As if there's anything left to damage!

515
00:22:44.180 --> 00:22:46.140
Vice Admiral Garp!

516
00:22:47.930 --> 00:22:49.470
Oh, Koby!

517
00:22:50.140 --> 00:22:51.890
You're okay!

518
00:22:54.140 --> 00:22:56.020
Thank goodness!

519
00:22:56.020 --> 00:22:58.400
They didn't kill him!

520
00:22:58.400 --> 00:23:00.030
Really now...

521
00:23:00.030 --> 00:23:01.530
He overdid it.

522
00:23:01.530 --> 00:23:04.400
You're such a naughty boy, Garp!

523
00:23:04.400 --> 00:23:08.370
Garp said Koby's the future of
the Marines. I won't stand for it!

524
00:23:08.370 --> 00:23:10.580
I'm gonna sabotage him!

525
00:23:10.580 --> 00:23:15.080
That's something you're supposed
to keep to yourself, you spoiled brat.

526
00:23:15.080 --> 00:23:16.710
It's cuter that way.

527
00:23:16.710 --> 00:23:18.790
Koby!

528
00:23:18.790 --> 00:23:21.090
Captain Koby!

529
00:23:21.420 --> 00:23:23.550
Koby!

530
00:23:23.550 --> 00:23:25.260
Tashigi!

531
00:23:25.630 --> 00:23:28.010
Even non-SWORD members came...

532
00:23:29.140 --> 00:23:32.100
Hey, Koby! Why are you
lugging that thing around?

533
00:23:32.100 --> 00:23:33.430
Vice Admiral Garp!

534
00:23:33.850 --> 00:23:37.520
We've tried everything,
but we can't get the shackle off!!

535
00:23:37.520 --> 00:23:38.480
Please...

536
00:23:40.860 --> 00:23:42.190
do...

537
00:23:42.780 --> 00:23:44.030
some...

538
00:23:45.150 --> 00:23:46.780
thing...

539
00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:52.080
Hibari...!

540
00:23:52.080 --> 00:23:53.290
Hibari!

541
00:23:56.670 --> 00:23:57.960
Hibari!

542
00:24:10.010 --> 00:24:11.260
Kuzan.

543
00:24:11.760 --> 00:24:13.220
Kuzan!

544
00:24:13.560 --> 00:24:14.980
What are you doing?!

545
00:24:14.980 --> 00:24:17.480
Please thaw her out right now!

546
00:24:19.060 --> 00:24:21.060
It's Aokiji!

547
00:24:21.690 --> 00:24:24.190
Captain Kuzan!

548
00:24:24.190 --> 00:24:26.030
Kuzan!

549
00:24:27.400 --> 00:24:29.280
Don't get me in trouble, Koby.

550
00:24:29.280 --> 00:24:31.200
I can't have you running off...

551
00:24:31.620 --> 00:24:34.330
while Teach is away.

552
00:24:35.040 --> 00:24:40.830
Two years ago, Admiral Akainu and Admiral Aokiji...

553
00:24:41.420 --> 00:24:47.510
fought for the position of the next
fleet admiral of Marine Headquarters.

554
00:24:51.640 --> 00:24:56.020
The deadly struggle went on for
ten days before a victor emerged:

555
00:24:56.680 --> 00:24:57.730
Akainu.

556
00:24:59.440 --> 00:25:04.020
However, Aokiji refused to serve under him.

557
00:25:04.400 --> 00:25:06.400
And so, he left the Marines.

558
00:25:12.530 --> 00:25:17.500
Some Island, New World

559
00:25:26.300 --> 00:25:28.380
What the...?!

560
00:25:28.720 --> 00:25:30.510
Blackbeard's here!

561
00:25:30.510 --> 00:25:33.300
Run! Get out of the town!

562
00:25:33.300 --> 00:25:34.220
Hey!

563
00:25:34.220 --> 00:25:36.430
What happened here?

564
00:25:36.430 --> 00:25:39.390
Wait! Who did this?!

565
00:25:43.520 --> 00:25:45.980
No, I don't need to ask...

566
00:25:47.320 --> 00:25:52.740
There's only one person
in the world who could've done this!

567
00:25:54.700 --> 00:25:56.160
It's you!

568
00:25:56.160 --> 00:25:58.200
Aokiji!

569
00:26:10.800 --> 00:26:13.430
My crew is frozen solid outside!

570
00:26:13.430 --> 00:26:15.850
Undo it!

571
00:26:16.720 --> 00:26:19.310
You're annoying me.

572
00:26:20.310 --> 00:26:22.940
And don't even think about using your power.

573
00:26:24.440 --> 00:26:26.730
Your crew will shatter and die.

574
00:26:28.230 --> 00:26:31.490
You're their captain, so I think you know.

575
00:26:32.740 --> 00:26:35.200
Do you really think I started it?

576
00:26:35.950 --> 00:26:38.910
Besides, you already know, don't you?

577
00:26:39.660 --> 00:26:43.830
I'm not just heartbroken, I'm furious.

578
00:26:45.880 --> 00:26:48.800
Take a guess who actually started this.

579
00:27:12.610 --> 00:27:15.070
Another round over here!

580
00:27:16.780 --> 00:27:19.870
You can really knock 'em back, Ice Pop!

581
00:27:19.870 --> 00:27:22.620
You're not bad yourself, you son of a bitch!

582
00:27:25.080 --> 00:27:28.210
So what did Akainu say next?

583
00:27:31.840 --> 00:27:34.970
"Two men who enlisted the same year
in a fight to the death...

584
00:27:34.970 --> 00:27:38.180
My eyes are burning with tears."

585
00:27:38.890 --> 00:27:41.890
And I said, "Yeah, that's 'cause...

586
00:27:42.220 --> 00:27:44.930
your magma's flowing!"

587
00:27:47.100 --> 00:27:48.610
And now look at me!

588
00:27:52.530 --> 00:27:54.490
I'm down to one leg!

589
00:27:55.400 --> 00:27:58.360
So that's what happens
when two admirals fight!

590
00:27:58.360 --> 00:27:59.910
What about Akainu?

591
00:28:00.450 --> 00:28:02.830
Did you at least rip one of his arms off?!

592
00:28:03.200 --> 00:28:04.200
No...

593
00:28:06.920 --> 00:28:09.540
But I'm sure he's scarred to all hell.

594
00:28:12.130 --> 00:28:16.470
Speaking of scars, he might know
Burn Scar, Commodore.

595
00:28:16.840 --> 00:28:18.970
Huh? Burn Scar?

596
00:28:18.970 --> 00:28:24.770
There are four important
red lode poneglyphs in the world.

597
00:28:26.890 --> 00:28:31.560
Big Mom and Kaido have two of them...

598
00:28:33.190 --> 00:28:37.530
But we can't find the other two!

599
00:28:37.530 --> 00:28:40.280
Once more fate rears its head...

600
00:28:40.280 --> 00:28:41.240
Yeah...

601
00:28:41.240 --> 00:28:47.250
And they say that the Man with
the Burn Scar has one of them.

602
00:28:48.960 --> 00:28:50.120
Is it me?

603
00:28:50.120 --> 00:28:52.500
You just got that scar, you idiot!

604
00:28:57.170 --> 00:28:59.180
Rumor has it...

605
00:29:05.470 --> 00:29:10.310
that he sails a pitch-black ship.

606
00:29:17.280 --> 00:29:22.990
And when you get close, he creates
a giant whirlpool to swallow you up.

607
00:29:27.790 --> 00:29:30.500
He may have eaten a devil fruit...

608
00:29:31.120 --> 00:29:34.710
I believe he works for the government.

609
00:29:35.210 --> 00:29:38.760
The World Government has
dark secrets, after all.

610
00:29:38.760 --> 00:29:41.630
If they hold on to even one of the stones,

611
00:29:41.630 --> 00:29:50.180
it means that no pirate will ever reach the
One Piece, the single greatest hidden treasure.

612
00:29:51.690 --> 00:29:55.570
The poneglyphs... I only have
bitter memories involving them.

613
00:29:55.570 --> 00:30:01.240
If I saw a red stone like that
in Ohara, I'd remember it.

614
00:30:02.860 --> 00:30:04.990
All I can remember...

615
00:30:04.990 --> 00:30:08.240
is a good friend who rebelled
against the government...

616
00:30:08.240 --> 00:30:11.080
and a girl with eyes full of despair...

617
00:30:11.580 --> 00:30:15.340
whose fate was in my hands.

618
00:30:17.670 --> 00:30:20.550
What kind of boring story is that?!

619
00:30:23.380 --> 00:30:25.600
Commodore, what should we do?

620
00:30:25.600 --> 00:30:26.220
Huh?

621
00:30:26.600 --> 00:30:30.930
If we take his power for ourselves,
it'll be a considerable asset to us...

622
00:30:36.400 --> 00:30:39.360
I heard that, you slimy bastards!

623
00:30:41.570 --> 00:30:45.530
How about I send you to an icy hell?!

624
00:30:49.080 --> 00:30:50.450
Stop, stop, stop!

625
00:30:52.000 --> 00:30:57.790
That's right, I've already heard about
you guys hunting devil fruit powers.

626
00:30:59.210 --> 00:31:00.960
Bring it on!

627
00:31:06.590 --> 00:31:07.800
Wait!

628
00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:09.930
I'm sorry!

629
00:31:09.930 --> 00:31:12.680
What my crew member said was ridiculous.

630
00:31:13.310 --> 00:31:15.850
I wouldn't dream of doing that.

631
00:31:15.850 --> 00:31:17.980
What I really wanted to ask you was...

632
00:31:17.980 --> 00:31:20.440
Do you wanna sail with us?

633
00:31:21.400 --> 00:31:24.650
What?! Captain, are you off your rocker?!

634
00:31:24.650 --> 00:31:27.620
You lost your position, didn't you?

635
00:31:27.620 --> 00:31:29.620
Do you have a place to go?

636
00:31:29.620 --> 00:31:31.620
What are you gonna do now?

637
00:31:31.620 --> 00:31:34.040
The guardians of justice have abandoned you!

638
00:31:35.080 --> 00:31:37.210
Man, this must be rock bottom.

639
00:31:37.210 --> 00:31:41.090
A pirate worrying about my prospects.

640
00:31:41.090 --> 00:31:44.300
Wherever you go, whatever you do,

641
00:31:44.920 --> 00:31:48.050
trouble will always find you!

642
00:31:48.050 --> 00:31:53.220
So what flag are you gonna fight under?

643
00:31:53.220 --> 00:31:54.640
Huh?!

644
00:31:56.020 --> 00:31:59.020
I'm different from the Marines!

645
00:31:59.020 --> 00:32:01.860
I have my own brand of justice!

646
00:32:01.860 --> 00:32:03.190
Don't be stupid!

647
00:32:03.190 --> 00:32:08.200
Just because we shared a few drinks
doesn't mean I trust scum like you!

648
00:32:08.200 --> 00:32:09.570
Whoa, whoa!

649
00:32:09.570 --> 00:32:12.450
I think you have the wrong idea about pirates.

650
00:32:12.450 --> 00:32:16.460
It's not like we're all buddies here!

651
00:32:21.630 --> 00:32:23.840
The only thing a pirate crew needs...

652
00:32:26.510 --> 00:32:30.680
is to have mutual interests!

653
00:32:33.560 --> 00:32:36.680
You're free now...

654
00:32:38.190 --> 00:32:40.100
so what do you wanna do?

655
00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:56.290
Hey, Kuzan!

656
00:32:56.750 --> 00:32:58.580
Thaw out Hibari!

657
00:32:59.120 --> 00:33:00.920
Let Koby escape!

658
00:33:00.920 --> 00:33:03.630
Come back to the Marines!

659
00:33:06.380 --> 00:33:11.510
You haven't changed at all.
Always saying what's on your mind.

660
00:33:15.220 --> 00:33:19.310
But I can't let any of that happen, Garp!

661
00:33:20.230 --> 00:33:22.020
I've always loved...

662
00:33:22.900 --> 00:33:24.730
how straightforward you are...

663
00:33:25.360 --> 00:33:29.650
which is why I'm living the way I want to now!

664
00:33:26.650 --> 00:33:29.650
Kuzan
Captain of the Tenth Ship
Blackbeard Pirates

665
00:33:34.870 --> 00:33:36.240
Bonehead...

666
00:33:52.970 --> 00:33:53.800
Ice...

667
00:33:54.300 --> 00:33:55.510
Ball!

668
00:34:01.770 --> 00:34:03.730
Vice Admiral Garp!

669
00:34:05.900 --> 00:34:07.730
Vice Admiral Garp!

670
00:34:11.200 --> 00:34:13.820
In order to save your beloved protégé,

671
00:34:14.410 --> 00:34:18.910
can you kill your former star pupil?!

672
00:34:20.620 --> 00:34:22.830
Don't live in the past, you moron!

673
00:34:24.460 --> 00:34:27.710
I taught you to live in the moment!

674
00:34:33.090 --> 00:34:34.180
It didn't work!

675
00:34:54.410 --> 00:34:56.160
Listen, Kuzan!

676
00:35:19.350 --> 00:35:21.560
Wavering is a sign...

677
00:35:23.310 --> 00:35:24.270
of weakness!

678
00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:29.900
Blue Hole!

679
00:35:58.890 --> 00:36:02.600
Meanwhile, at Winner Island...

680
00:35:58.890 --> 00:36:04.060
Winner Island
New World

681
00:36:39.390 --> 00:36:44.270
You can hardly call yourself
a pirate crew without a ship!

682
00:36:44.770 --> 00:36:47.480
There's no way for you to escape!

683
00:36:48.100 --> 00:36:54.360
The hundred pirates whose hearts
you stole at Rocky Port...

684
00:36:54.360 --> 00:36:58.950
are still living in fear on the Pirate Island!

685
00:36:59.320 --> 00:37:05.540
But if I bring them your heart,
they're sure to raise a toast!

686
00:37:12.420 --> 00:37:14.670
You really made it for me!

687
00:37:14.670 --> 00:37:18.630
But I can't guarantee it'll work.

688
00:37:24.390 --> 00:37:26.020
Now...

689
00:37:26.020 --> 00:37:30.390
I'm having a hard time deciding whether
to sell or use the Op-Op Fruit.

690
00:37:30.390 --> 00:37:33.610
It can even grant me eternal youth, can't it?!

691
00:37:41.360 --> 00:37:44.120
Get your hands...

692
00:37:46.240 --> 00:37:48.000
off my captain!

693
00:37:57.710 --> 00:37:58.880
Bepo...

694
00:38:04.720 --> 00:38:06.850
What?! Sulong?!

695
00:38:06.850 --> 00:38:09.310
No way! The moon isn't even out!

696
00:38:18.860 --> 00:38:20.860
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

697
00:38:37.170 --> 00:38:38.210
Captain!

698
00:39:00.030 --> 00:39:02.320
Dammit! They fled to sea!

699
00:39:02.320 --> 00:39:04.530
Don't let him get away!

700
00:39:11.500 --> 00:39:14.080
Go back, Bepo...

701
00:39:18.540 --> 00:39:22.840
I can't... leave the crew... behind...

702
00:39:22.840 --> 00:39:24.590
I won't go back!

703
00:39:25.340 --> 00:39:27.720
Trust them, Captain!

704
00:39:27.720 --> 00:39:30.510
From that frigid northern port
all the way until now...

705
00:39:32.520 --> 00:39:35.900
we've always survived!

706
00:39:35.900 --> 00:39:37.190
So...

707
00:39:38.480 --> 00:39:40.980
none of us will die here!

708
00:39:46.740 --> 00:39:49.490
We've overcome so much together!

709
00:39:51.580 --> 00:39:53.450
So, Captain!

710
00:39:54.540 --> 00:39:57.120
Don't die!

711
00:40:05.880 --> 00:40:07.470
Please...

712
00:40:08.840 --> 00:40:10.850
don't die!

713
00:40:16.060 --> 00:40:19.770
At Winner Island in the New World...

714
00:40:28.320 --> 00:40:33.040
the Heart Pirates' submarine, the Polar Tang,

715
00:40:33.410 --> 00:40:34.910
was sunk.

716
00:40:38.370 --> 00:40:42.540
The Heart Pirates led by Trafalgar Law...

717
00:40:43.750 --> 00:40:45.260
were defeated.

718
00:40:54.210 --> 00:40:59.300
Running so long, lost track of just how long it’s been

719
00:41:00.150 --> 00:41:06.660
Collected scars while striving, not even trying, beneath my skin

720
00:41:07.160 --> 00:41:14.080
But in the back of my head the dream is not dead, I remember a map

721
00:41:14.160 --> 00:41:20.370
to a treasure still gleaming, it’s within our grasp

722
00:41:20.510 --> 00:41:27.280
Can you feel my heart? Feelings I impart

723
00:41:27.240 --> 00:41:34.390
The promises are there; they're deep down but still primed to share

724
00:41:34.520 --> 00:41:43.500
Peerless dreams kept close, the dreams that always matter most

725
00:41:43.680 --> 00:41:49.260
Before we set sail why not raise a toast?

726
00:41:49.370 --> 00:41:56.280
So I pen this note to you Dear sunrise, I’ll see you soon

727
00:41:56.440 --> 00:42:03.470
See the smile I saw the day that I sang this song to you

728
00:42:03.450 --> 00:42:10.520
And regardless of our age, these mem’ries will still remain

729
00:42:10.420 --> 00:42:17.630
Won’t forget until this wish makes it to you
